Stefan Bion wrote:
&gt;
&gt;  Hi all,
&gt;
&gt;  I&#39;m currently thinking about a new kind of &quot;spirit speaking machine&quot;.
&gt;  The idea is to build a kind of &quot;instrument&quot; for spirits to play on if
&gt;  they want to speak to us. Actually this has been the basic idea when
&gt;  I began to develop programs like Audio-Ed, Audigit, or EVPmaker.
&gt;  Phoneme synthesis was the easiest way to implement this, but actually
&gt;  I do think that formant synthesis is probably more appropriate for
&gt;  this purpose, since it does simulate the human vocal tract and thus
&gt;  is more &quot;natural&quot;. Perhaps this a more &quot;intuitive&quot; way for spirits to
&gt;  produce voices than by assembling sound fragments.

If I&#39;m understanding you correctly, I&#39;d say yes.  Most of the clear 
messages I get through my 469 seem to be more like standard evps - the 
sounds formed from the base energy as opposed to put together from 
separate syllables pulled off the airwaves.

Actually, this gives me an idea.  On the low tech end, I wonder if just 
using humming as a base would give the spirits the energy and 
frequencies they need to form the sounds of language.  I will play with 
this and let you know if that pans out.


Nellie

